cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on disfluency detection in speech transcripts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new model that uses a convolutional neural network (CNN) and a new auto-correlation operator, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses general-purpose methods for learning input representation, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
